<subSubSection id="C374652CFF95FFFED4CCFA910999FA0E" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FF95FFFED4CCFA910999FA0E" blockId="104.[151,1437,1194,2013]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF95FFFED4CCFA910C1AFAC7" bold="true" box="[199,322,1338,1364]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FF95FFFED5BAFA900FCBFAC6" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[433,659,1339,1365]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pensilvania" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF95FFFED5BAFA900FCBFAC6" box="[433,659,1339,1365]" italics="true" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Tenedos pensilvania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FF95FFFED691FA900F81FAC6" bold="true" box="[666,729,1339,1365]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFF95FFFED691FA900F81FAC6" box="[666,729,1339,1365]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, can be distinguished by concave median apophysis (MA) with hook-shaped appendix, anterior branch of retrolateral tibial apophysis (aRTA) represented by thin lamina, and by the presence of short and wide basal retrolateral tibial apophysis (bRTA) (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF95FFFED7DAFA280901FA0E" box="[977,1113,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 74" captionStartId="105.[151,250,1819,1843]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,527,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-153@105.[151,1436,525,1796]" captionTargetPageId="105" captionText="FIGURE 74. Tenedos pensilvania sp. n. A–B. Male habits (IAvH-I-657): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Prolateral. E. Retroventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–F: 500µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520958" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520958/files/figure.png" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Figs 74C–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FF95FFFED06EFA2909ECFA0E" box="[1125,1204,1410,1437]" captionStart="FIGURE 75" captionStartId="106.[151,250,1438,1462]" captionTargetBox="[159,1432,185,1414]" captionTargetId="figure-27@106.[151,1436,181,1415]" captionTargetPageId="106" captionText="FIGURE 75. Tenedos yurayaco sp. n. A, D. Male palp (IAvH-I-44):A. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. Tenedos marquetones sp. n. B, E. Male palp (IAvH-I-2973): B. Ventral view. E. Retrolateral view. Tenedos pensilvania sp. n. C, F. Male palp (IAvH- I-657): C. Ventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–F: 200µm. Abbreviations: aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis; bRTA, basal retrolateral tibial apophysis; pMA, posterior branch of the median; apophysis; pRTA, posterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520960" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520960/files/figure.png" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">75C, F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
